      "acceptanceCriteria": "Version-controlled solver with documented release notes and regression test suite covering core flow physics.",
      "rationale": "ANSYS Fluent 2022R1 used under institutional software QA plan. Release notes reviewed; regression tests passed for turbulent pipe flow and rotating machinery benchmarks. Version control logs archived."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Solver verified against at least one canonical benchmark with known analytical or manufactured solution.",
      "rationale": "Solver verified against Taylor-Couette flow analytical solution and lid-driven cavity benchmark at Re=1000. Observed order of accuracy consistent with nominal second-order scheme."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Grid convergence index (GCI) reported for primary QoI (hemolysis index) with GCI < 5% on fine grid, demonstrating mesh-independent solution.",
      "rationale": "Three mesh levels were generated (coarse: 2.1M, medium: 5.4M, fine: 11.8M cells). GCI for hemolysis index on the fine-to-medium ratio was 14.3%, exceeding the 5% acceptance threshold. The team noted the fine mesh was used for all production runs and judged the error acceptable for engineering purposes, but formal GCI convergence criterion is not satisfied. Richardson extrapolation was not applied."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental test conditions (flow rate, rotational speed, fluid properties) documented and traceable to calibrated instrumentation records.",
      "rationale": "FDA benchmark experimental data used. Flow rates (2.5–7.0 L/min) and rotational speeds (2000–3500 RPM) documented in PIV and hemolysis measurement protocols. Fluid properties (viscosity, density) verified against ASTM F1841 blood analog."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Predicted hemolysis index compared against experimental measurements with quantified agreement metric (e.g., normalized RMS error < 20%).",
      "rationale": "Predicted normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) compared against FDA benchmark experimental data across 5 operating points. Normalized RMS error of 17.4% observed, within acceptance threshold. Systematic over-prediction at high rotational speed noted and attributed to turbulence model limitations."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs used in validation (NIH, shear stress distribution) directly correspond to QoIs required for the COU decision (relative hemolysis index RH).",
      "rationale": "Normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) computed in validation directly informs the relative hemolysis index (RH) used in the COU acceptance criterion (RH < 1). Shear stress exposure time histograms validated against PIV-derived estimates. QoI mapping documented in credibility assessment plan."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation experiments conducted on geometrically similar pump under overlapping operating conditions to the COU.",
      "rationale": "FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry used for validation is the same geometry as the COU device. Operating conditions span the COU envelope (2.5–7.0 L/min, 2000–3500 RPM). Blood analog fluid properties match within 3% of clinical blood viscosity range."
    },
    {
